b"Flamin' Hot Dill Pickle Fried Pickles \xe2\x80\x93 we think they\xe2\x80\x99re a big dill. :cucumber::fire:

Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: Flamin\xe2\x80\x99 Hot Dill Pickle Crusted Pickles Recipe

Ingredients:
1 jar Thick-cut dill pickle chips or spears
1 bag Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: Flamin\xe2\x80\x99 Hot Dill Pickle flavored potato chips
2 Eggs + 1 Tbsp. Water
1 cup All-Purpose flour
\xc2\xbc cup Corn starch
1 tsp. Kosher salt
1 tsp. Garlic powder
\xc2\xbd tsp. Cayenne pepper
\xc2\xbc tsp. Black pepper
 
Instructions:
Pre-heat oven to 375 \xc2\xb0F.
Drain dill pickle chips or spears from pickle juice. Lightly pat pickles dry with a paper towel.
Crush the Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: Flamin\xe2\x80\x99 Hot dill Pickle chips, and pour into a shallow tray or plate.
In a bowl, make egg-wash by whisking together the eggs and water.
Make seasoned flour by mixing the flour and cornstarch with all spices and seasonings. Place into a shallow tray or plate.
Bread the dill pickles by lightly tossing in the seasoned flour. Shake off the excess, then dip into the egg-wash. Finally, coat the pickles with the crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered:, gently pressing the chip pieces to adhere to the pickles.
Transfer the crusted pickles onto a sheet tray lined with parchment paper.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes, or until the coating is crunchy, but chips are not burnt.
Allow to cool slightly before serving alongside your favorite dipping sauce!"

b'Chip or treat! Get into spooky SZN by making these Lay\xe2\x80\x99s chocolate-covered ghoulish treats. :ghost::woman_zombie_selector: Recipe below.\xc2\xa0

Ingredients:
One bag of Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Wavy chips 
\xc2\xbd cup of milk chocolate chips
\xc2\xbd cup of espresso chips
\xc2\xbd cup of white chocolate 
Coconut oil 
Edible candy eyes
Mixed sprinkles 
Colored food dye

Recipe: 
Place \xc2\xbd cup of milk chocolate chips with \xc2\xbd tablespoon of coconut oil in a microwave safe bowl. Heat in the microwave on 50% power level for 30 seconds until chocolate is melted. Do the same with the espresso chips and white chocolate, until all chocolate is melted. Add preferred food dye color to white chocolate and mix. 
Dip Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Wavy chips into chocolate as desired and lay on parchment paper to dry (espresso chocolate for bats, milk chocolate for monsters). Drizzle colored white chocolate on top to add some flare.
Top with edible eyes and sprinkles to make the bats and monsters.
Place in freezer for at least 30 minutes, until chocolate dries.
Enjoy!'

b"Lay's Poppables Creamy Jalape\xc3\xb1o? As a topping? On Mac and Cheese? Yes plz.

Get the recipe from @Bustle and @gilliehouston below :cheese_wedge:

Ingredients:
1-pound dried cavatappi pasta (or another short pasta)
6 tbsp unsalted butter, divided
1/2 medium yellow onion, diced
3 fresh jalape\xc3\xb1os, deseeded and diced
4 cloves garlic, minced
1/4 cup all-purpose flour
3 cups half-and-half
5 oz cream cheese
1 cup Colby Jack, Monterrey Jack, our Pepper Jack cheese, shredded
1 cup cheddar cheese, shredded
2 cups mozzarella cheese, shredded
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1/4 tsp cayenne powder (optional)
8 slices bacon, cooked and crumbled
2 cups LAY'S:registered: Poppables:trade_mark: Creamy Jalape\xc3\xb1o Flavored Potato Snacks

Recipe:
Preheat the oven to 350\xc2\xb0F. Add butter to a large saucepan over medium heat. Add diced onion and jalape\xc3\xb1o and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add garlic and cook 1 minute.
While the vegetables cook, add the pasta to a pot of boiling water and cook according to package instructions until just shy of al dente.
To the saucepan, stir in flour and cook for 2 minutes. Add in half-and-half, whisking until all flour lumps are gone. Cook for 7-8 minutes, stirring frequently, until the mixture has thickened.
Add in cubed cream cheese and stir until melted. Add in most of the shredded Jack, cheddar, and mozzarella cheese, reserving some for the topping. Stir until the cheese has melted and the sauce is creamy; if the sauce is too thick, add a splash of half-and-half or milk as needed. Add in salt, pepper, and cayenne and stir.
Remove the sauce from the heat and add in the drained pasta and most of the crumbled bacon, stirring until well combined. Transfer the pasta mixture to a greased casserole dish or large cast iron skillet.
For the crunchy topping, crush 2 cups LAY'S:registered: Poppables:trade_mark: Creamy Jalape\xc3\xb1o Flavored Potato Snacks to a coarse texture and combine with 3 tbsp melted butter.
Top the pasta with remaining cheese, bacon, and the LAY'S:registered: Poppables:trade_mark: Creamy Jalape\xc3\xb1o crumble. Bake 20-25 minutes until the topping is golden brown. Optional: top with sliced fresh jalape\xc3\xb1o. Serve, and enjoy"

b'Celebrate Hispanic Heritage Month and give your esquites an extra kick by adding Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Kettle Cooked Flamin\xe2\x80\x99 Hot chips. :ear_of_corn: Recipe below!

ESQUITES (MEXICAN CORN SALAD)
 
1 cups fresh corn kernels, just cut from cob
1 tablespoons unsalted butter
1/4 teaspoon salt
1 tablespoons mayonnaise (low fat is fine) or Mexican crema
2 tablespoons queso fresco or cotija cheese, crumbled
1 lime cut into wedges (optional)
\xc2\xbd cup crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Kettle Cooked Flamin\xe2\x80\x99 Hot chips
 
1. Heat the butter in a pan.
2. Add the corn kernels and salt. Saut\xc3\xa9 for another 4 minutes and remove from heat. Let the mixture cool slightly and stir the mayonnaise in. Move to a serving bowl.
3. Layer into the bowl one layer of corn, followed by a layer of crumbled queso fresco or cotija cheese, and then a layer of crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Kettle Cooked Flamin\xe2\x80\x99 Hot chips. Repeat so you end up with six layers total.
4. Top with fresh squeezed lime juice.'

b'Milkshake and fries may have met their match with Ice Cream Sandwiches topped with Lay\xe2\x80\x99s chips. :drooling_face:

LAY\xe2\x80\x99S:registered: ICE CREAM SANDWICHES: 

Sandwich a scoop of your favorite ice cream between two Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: Chocolate Chip Cookies, dip or drizzle with chocolate, and roll in sprinkles and crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered:! 
 
Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: Chocolate Chip Cookies recipe below: 

Ingredients: 
1 bag crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: Kettle Cooked Original Potato Chips or Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: Classic 
2 sticks (1 cup) Butter, unsalted, softened 
\xc2\xbe cup Brown Sugar 
\xc2\xbe cup Granulated Sugar 
1 tsp. Vanilla Extract 
2 Eggs 
2 \xc2\xbc cups All Purpose Flour 
1 tsp. Baking Soda 
\xc2\xbe tsp. Kosher Salt 
1 \xc2\xbd cup Semi-Sweet Chocolate chips 
 
Instructions: 
Preheat oven at 350 \xc2\xb0F. 
Beat together room temperature butter and both kinds of sugar, on high speed, until light and fluffy (2-3 minutes). 
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, and beat on medium speed until just combined. 
Combine all dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, and salt) and add to the mixer. Mix on low speed until just combined. 
Stir in approximately half of the crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: potato chips (reserve the rest for coating) and the chocolate chips. Fold to incorporate. 
Refrigerate until dough is chilled. 
Scoop dough into approximate 3 Tbsp. balls. Press down lightly to flatten slightly, and roll/coat in the remaining crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered:. 
Place cookies 2 in. apart on a parchment-lined baking sheet. 
Bake for approximately 12-14  minutes, or until edges are set and lightly golden. 
Allow to cool on baking sheet before serving and enjoying!'

b'We put the "chip" in these Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Chocolate Chip Cookies. Recipe below! :cookie:

Ingredients: 
:black_small_square_selector: Approx. 4 cups Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: Classic Potato Chips (13 oz. party-sized bag, crushed 1/8 in-1/4 in. ) 
:black_small_square_selector: 2 sticks (1 cup) Butter, unsalted, softened 
:black_small_square_selector:3/4 cup Light Brown Sugar
:black_small_square_selector:3\xe2\x81\x844 cup Granulated Sugar
:black_small_square_selector:1 tsp. Vanilla Extract 
:black_small_square_selector:2 Eggs
:black_small_square_selector:2 1\xe2\x81\x844 cups All Purpose Flour
:black_small_square_selector:1 tsp. Baking Soda
:black_small_square_selector:3\xe2\x81\x844 tsp. Kosher Salt
:black_small_square_selector:1 1\xe2\x81\x842 cups Semi-Sweet Chocolate chips 

Preparation:
-Preheat oven at 325 F. 
-Beat together room temperature butter and both kinds of sugar, on high speed, until light and fluffy (2-3 minutes).
-Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, and beat on medium speed until just combined.
-Combine all dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, and salt) and add to the mixer. Mix on low speed until just combined.
-Stir in approximately half of the crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered: potato chips (reserve the rest for coating) and the chocolate chips. Fold to incorporate. 
-Refrigerate until dough is chilled.
-Scoop dough into approximate 2-3 Tbsp. balls. Press down lightly to flatten slightly, and roll/coat in the remaining crushed Lay\xe2\x80\x99s:registered:.
-Place cookies 2 inches apart on a parchment- lined baking sheet.
-Bake for approximately 13 minutes, or until edges are set and lightly golden.
-Allow to cool completely on baking sheet, serve, and enjoy!
-(Add a light dusting of fine flour salt or fleur de sel can be added post-bake to bring out the sweet/salty flavor combo from the potato chips).'

b"Mac N Cheese just got an upgrade. Enter Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Salt & Vinegar Mac n Cheese.

Ingredients: 
1 bag of LAY'S:registered: Salt & Vinegar Potato Chips 
1 pound elbow macaroni 
8 Tablespoons butter 
\xc2\xbc cup flour
4 cups milk 
\xc2\xbc teaspoon dried thyme 
1/8 teaspoon or a pinch of nutmeg 
1 \xc2\xbd tsp of salt 
pinch of cayenne pepper 
2 cups shredded cheddar cheese 
1 cup shredded Gruy\xc3\xa8re cheese 
\xc2\xbc teaspoon dry mustard 
1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese 
2 tablespoons dry breadcrumbs 

-Cook the macaroni in boiling water. Drain and set aside.
-Melt 4 Tbps of the butter in a saucepan over low heat. 
-Stir in the flour. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring. Slowly pour in the milk, whisking consistently to prevent clumps.
-Stir in the thyme, nutmeg, salt and cayenne pepper. Simmer for 10 minutes until sauce starts to thicken. Remove from heat. 
-Combine the sauce with the Cheddar cheese, Gruy\xc3\xa8re cheese and mustard. Cook, stirring for 3 minutes or until the cheese melts. 
-Crumble the LAY'S:registered: Salt & Vinegar Flavored Potato Chips. Combine with Parmesan cheese, breadcrumbs and remaining 4 Tbsp of butter in a large saucepan. Stir over medium heat for 5 minutes, until golden brown. 
-Combine the macaroni with the cheese sauce. Spoon into four bowls. Top with the potato-chip topping and enjoy! 
-Combine the macaroni with the cheese sauce. Spoon into four ramekins. Top with the potato-chip topping and enjoy!"

b'Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Wavy meet Jalapeno Popper Dip:collision:

Make it for your long weekend ahead! :right_arrow_curving_down_selector:

Dip
8\xc2\xa0oz\xc2\xa0cream cheese, soft
1\xc2\xa0c.\xc2\xa0sour cream
1\xc2\xa0tsp\xc2\xa0garlic powder
1 c.\xc2\xa0shredded cheddar cheese
1 c.\xc2\xa0shredded Monterrey Jack cheese
\xc2\xbe\xc2\xa0c.\xc2\xa0shredded Parmesan cheese
~6\xc2\xa0oz of diced jalapenos,\xc2\xa0drained

Topping
1\xc2\xa0c.\xc2\xa0Panko bread crumbs
4\xc2\xa0Tbsp\xc2\xa0melted butter
1\xc2\xa0Tbsp\xc2\xa0fresh parsley\xc2\xa0minced
\xc2\xbc\xc2\xa0c.\xc2\xa0shredded Parmesan cheese

Recipe:
Heat oven to 375 degrees.
In a bowl, combine and mix the cream cheese, garlic powder and sour cream until whipped. Add cheddar cheese, Monterrey Jack cheese, \xc2\xbe c. Parmesan cheese and jalape\xc3\xb1os, mix until combined.
Spread into an 8x8 inch greased baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine the topping ingredients. Spread over the top of the dip mixture in dish. 
Bake 17-20 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Add jalape\xc3\xb1os on top.
Serve with Lay\xe2\x80\x99s Wavy and enjoy!'
